# Styles

- Design tokens (`assets/css/base/_tokens.scss`) are CSS custom properties, not SCSS
  variables — this is what makes light/dark theme switching a matter of overriding
  property values rather than compiling two stylesheets.
- One file per component under `assets/css/components/`; a component file only styles
  its own DOM subtree, never reaches into layout-level concerns.
- Layout skeleton (`grid.scss`, `header.scss`, `footer.scss`) is separate from component
  styling — layout positions things, components style themselves.
- `assets/css/main.scss` contains only `@use`/`@forward` statements in cascade order
  (base → layout → components → themes) — never add rules directly to it.
- Themes (`themes/light.scss`, `themes/dark.scss`) only override token values under
  `[data-theme="..."]` selectors — no component-specific overrides there; if a component
  needs theme-aware styling beyond a token swap, that logic belongs in the component's
  own file, referencing the tokens.
- Use SCSS via Hugo Pipes (Dart Sass), not LESS — this project reimplements Vector's
  design independently rather than transpiling its LESS source.
